<td background="./site/pict/fondmenu.gif" height="150" valign="top">
Donc Plane of power est une nouvelle extension de... 18 zones et 2 villes... enfin je dirai plutot 18 plans et 2 villes planaires qui feront des liens entre les differents plans... Je sais pas comment le KGC va s´amuser avec tout ça lol<br><br>Le systeme de progression des joueurs va se trouver de nouveau modifié sur les plans, bien sur il faudra etre level 46 pour monter sur ce plans...<br><br>plusieurs centaines de nouveaux mobs et d´objets ainsi que beaucoup de quetes ;)<br><br>Tres important : des histoires RP completes seront relatés aux plans LOL<br><br><font color='#FF0000'><B>Annoncé pour le 1er octobre</b></font>, y rajouter les retards, la semaine de patch plus celles de patchs d'urgence et l'import en france :)<br><br>Les plans pour l´instant annoncés :<br><br><B>The Plane of Flame</b><br><br><A href=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/planeofflamepano.jpg target=blank><img border=0 src=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/planeofflamepano_tn.jpg></a><br><br>Solusek Ro, The Burning Prince with his crown of flame and spear of fire, rules the Plane of Flame from his mighty Burning Tower. Fire Elementals, Efreeti, and an assortment of other fire-loving planar creatures inhabit Solusek?s endless kingdom of blazing landscapes under a burning red sky filled with clouds of smoke, smoldering embers, and fiery rain. <br><br>The mortals attribute to Solusek such acts as the raising of the Serpent?s Spine Mountains and the destruction of Eldarr Forest, creating the Deserts of Ro and changing the face and history of Norrath. Does this deity, revered by powerful wizards throughout Norrath, serve the will of his father, the mysterious greater god Fennin Ro, Tyrant of Fire and Lord of the Plane of Fire? Or does Solusek Ro serve his own destructive and power-hungry cause?<br><br><B>Plane of Disease</b> - The putrid stench of rotting flesh hangs heavy in the air as adventurers discover a vast plane of pestilence, decay, and corruption. <br><br><B>Plane of Justice</b> - A stark prison zone where the Tribunal sits in judgment. Adventurers will find the prison´s orderly yet confining environment a challenge to chaotic souls.<br><br><B>Plane of Nightmares</b> - The home of Terris Thule. A forested region, a wilderness of terror, the Plane of Nightmares will steal the sleep of many adventurers.<br><br><B>Plane of Knowledge</b> - New Tanaan is a city-state that exists outside normal physical and political boundaries, a haven of knowledge for those who seek it.<br><br><B>Plane of Tranquility</b> - Tranquility, the gateway to deeper planar realms. Peace reigns supreme here and adventurers will not be able to engage in combat or use offensive magics.<br><br><br>Quelques Screenshots :<br><center><br>Pas beau lui :<br><A href=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/Fly_Man_InGame3.jpg target=blank><img border=0 src=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/Fly_Man_InGame3_lo.jpg></a><br><br>Huk :<br><A href=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/trollproc.jpg target=blank><img border=0 src=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/trollproc_thumb.jpg></a><br><br>Mignone :<br><A href=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/Nymph_InGame2.jpg target=blank><img border=0 src=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/images/Nymph_InGame2_lo.jpg></a><br></center><br><br>Source : <a href=http://everquest.station.sony.com/power/ target=blank>http://www.planesofpower.com</a>. Merci a Dodger d'avoir remarqué la mise a jour du site ;)</td >
